{"schema":"algviz/1","title":"Edit Distance","topic":"dynamic-programming","code":["public int MinDistance(string a, string b)","{","    int m = a.Length, n = b.Length;","    var dp = new int[m + 1, n + 1];","    for (int i = 0; i <= m; i++) dp[i, 0] = i;","    for (int j = 0; j <= n; j++) dp[0, j] = j;","    for (int i = 1; i <= m; i++)","        for (int j = 1; j <= n; j++)","            dp[i, j] = a[i - 1] == b[j - 1]","                ? dp[i - 1, j - 1]","                : 1 + Math.Min(dp[i - 1, j - 1],","                      Math.Min(dp[i - 1, j], dp[i, j - 1]));","    return dp[m, n];","}"],"structures":{"dp":{"type":"grid","label":"dp[i, j] = edits to turn a[0..i-1] into b[0..j-1]"}},"frames":[{"line":4,"caption":"Base case: dp[0,0] = 0 — turning the empty string into the empty string costs nothing. The base column and base row grow out from here.","note":"Edit Distance is the textbook 2D string DP. State: dp[i][j] = the minimum insert/delete/replace edits to convert the first i chars of a into the first j chars of b. The two base lines are free, and every interior cell is built from three already-known neighbours — so one forward sweep fills the table.","vars":{"a":"\"horse\"","b":"\"ros\""},"result":null,"states":{"dp":{"type":"grid","rows":6,"cols":4,"cells":[{"key":"r0c0","value":0,"highlight":"active"},{"key":"r0c1","value":0},{"key":"r0c2","value":0},{"key":"r0c3","value":0},{"key":"r1c0","value":0},{"key":"r1c1","value":0},{"key":"r1c2","value":0},{"key":"r1c3","value":0},{"key":"r2c0","value":0},{"key":"r2c1","value":0},{"key":"r2c2","value":0},{"key":"r2c3","value":0},{"key":"r3c0","value":0},{"key":"r3c1","value":0},{"key":"r3c2","value":0},{"key":"r3c3","value":0},{"key":"r4c0","value":0},{"key":"r4c1","value":0},{"key":"r4c2","value":0},{"key":"r4c3","value":0},{"key":"r5c0","value":0},{"key":"r5c1","value":0},{"key":"r5c2","value":0},{"key":"r5c3","value":0}],"rowHeader":["·","h","o","r","s","e"],"colHeader":["·","r","o","s"]}}},{"line":5,"capti